# Accepted trivy misconfigurations for terraform-aws-minecraft.
#
# This is a low-cost, personal, scale-to-zero Minecraft server. The findings
# below are deliberate design tradeoffs, not exposures. Runtime security relies
# on the game-port-only ingress security group plus the Minecraft whitelist and
# online-mode (see README), not on network isolation.

# AWS-0104: Egress to 0.0.0.0/0 is required — the container pulls its image and
# reaches Mojang/Microsoft auth and mod sources over the public internet.
AVD-AWS-0104

# AWS-0164: Public IP on the task subnet is intentional. The design avoids a NAT
# gateway (~$32/mo) and the watchdog points DNS at the task's public IP. Inbound
# is restricted to the single game port.
AVD-AWS-0164

# AWS-0178: VPC flow logs omitted — added log-storage cost for negligible value
# on a single-task VPC.
AVD-AWS-0178

# AWS-0017: CloudWatch log groups use default AWS-managed encryption at rest. A
# customer-managed KMS key adds cost and key management not warranted for game,
# DNS-query, and launcher logs.
AVD-AWS-0017

# AWS-0034: Container Insights left disabled to avoid extra CloudWatch cost on a
# personal server.
AVD-AWS-0034

# AWS-0066: X-Ray tracing omitted on the tiny start/stop launcher Lambda.
AVD-AWS-0066
